
It's possible to use autotools or cmake to configure libdodo's build options.

[Autotools]
	To configure run ./configure with additional options you can find running './configure --help' or some of them you can find in build.options file.

[CMake]
	To configure run 'cmake .' with additional options you can find in build.options file.

You may edit include/libdodo/directives.h to tune some options.

To compile use 'gmake'
To install 'gmake install'
